user.biography: Dad of Lyric & Ruby. I wear tights again. My toenails get painted when I fall asleep. I play a Viking named Kjetill. Miss the SuperSonics. Go Leafs Go

node.text: The story of lil ol Edge returning to the ring after 9 years. A story we ALL thought would never happen. The whole process caught on film by happy accident. Streaming on @wwenetwork now, featuring music by the legendary @foofighters #wwe24 #walk #lastmanstanding #wrestlemania

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam “Edge” Copeland in Rocket Mortgage FieldHouse. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: I know what you’re saying. Why did you post a picture of a hallway? This hallway was instrumental to E&C and The Hardy Boyz taking flight. Some backstory, so bear with me. No Mercy 99, Gund Arena in Cleveland. I was living in the Bahamas(don’t ask), and got stuck in Miami the night before the ppv because of a hurricane. I woke up and realized I needed to drive through the hurricane, get to Tampa where I could make a flight to Cleveland that landed at 3, and got me to the arena at 4. Our match was at 7:30.  When I got to the arena, I raced in a sweaty, stressed mess and found Jay, Matt and Jeff huddled in this hallway. I joined, we put our demented minds together and the tag team ladder match was born. Which propelled us to where we all are now, still going strong 22 years later. After that match we all came back to this hallway and had a beer. Which we all hate but seemed fitting. So yeah, this hallway is special to me, as silly as it sounds, and I got to spend some time there again yesterday and reflect. If I didn’t make that flight who knows how different my career might have been. What a ride.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam “Edge” Copeland in Dickies Arena. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text: What a week. Feel like I got run over by an 18 wheeler carrying elephants. But having all of you back screaming your heads off was the reminder that, for me, this is the best job in the world. And no matter the outcome, just know that when I’m in there, there’s no phoning it in, I’ll give ya everything I have. Which is so much easier to do when I can hear all of you. Let’s keep movin!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam “Edge” Copeland in Dickies Arena. May be an image of 3 people and crowd.

node.text: Today at #mitb I go for the Dirty Dozen. 12 World Championships. Against the best in this business. Let’s go.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam “Edge” Copeland in Houston, Texas. May be an image of 1 person, child, standing, outdoors and text that says 'ocky mtns. COLORADO MOMMY & ME BEST FINS FOREVER EDGE IS MY HERO'.

node.text: I saw this lil Peanut as I came out to the ring last night. A friend sent me this photo of her from earlier in the day before the show. She’s probably the same age as my Ruby and the thought that I could be part of a character that makes her feel good? Man, THAT’S why we do it. Never got a chance to meet her, but just know I saw you!! Houston, not the end result we wanted, but what a night and experience having all of you back. Now, on to #mitb

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam “Edge” Copeland on July 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and crowd.

node.text: This Friday I get to do something I never thought I’d do again. Share a ring with @619iamlucha and team with his son @dominik_35 for the first time ever. I don’t want this to get too syrupy but let’s face it, I don’t know how much longer Rey or I do this crazy thing called wrestling. I do know the window is closing. So this Friday on Smackdown, I’m gonna savor it. I get to share the ring, maybe for the last time, with my dear friend who I can honestly say I love. We’ve been through a lot together over the years. We’ve won tag team titles together, battled each other(one of my favorite opponents), laughed until we cried and lost dear friends. But I know that chemistry we’ve had since day one will still be there. Rey is a living legend. It’s tossed around too much, but in this case it is without one iota of a doubt, true. And to be here for even a tiny part of Dom’s ride? Man, I’m so proud to go out there with them. In front of our people. Finally. Can’t wait Houston. Can’t wait.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam “Edge” Copeland on July 12, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text.

node.text: As a child and burgeoning wrestling fanatic, Paul “Mr #1derful” Orndorff was the first wrestler I despised. And feared. He was the most intense wrestler I’ve ever seen. To this day. I went to the Big Event in Toronto at CNE Stadium. 75,000 fans, all to see Orndorff vs Hulk Hogan. I’ll never forget it. I have this poster, which my mom took from the Becker’s convenience store she worked at(Canadians will chuckle at that reference), and I have it hanging on the wall at my ring to this day. Fast forward many years later, and I found myself in the lobby of our hotel on the morning before WrestleMania 21 getting ready to hit the gym with Hulk. Who saunters out of the elevator in his flip flops to join us but Paul Orndorff. I had no idea this was coming. Even on the eve of winning the first MITB, it blew my mind that I was doing lat pull downs with Mr. Wonderful and The Hulkster. Another memory I will never forget. Or the memories he supplied me with his abilities. Rest in absolute Power Paul.

node.text: My roomful of rainbows that is Ruby is 5 today. Man. That flew. Here she’s contemplating the release of this years butterflies. And game 7 tonight😳I am so proud of her and her infectious way of bringing smiles wherever she goes. Also kid has some serious delt game.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam “Edge” Copeland in Asheville, North Carolina. May be a black-and-white image of 1 person.

node.text: Am I going through my Beck, Sea Change phase? My version of a Simon & Garfunkel album cover? Attempting an Astrid Kirchherr photo? Nope. Just chillin  on the canvas I paint on. A new #wwechronicle streams on @peacocktv in the US and @wwenetwork worldwide this Saturday right after #wrestlemania night 1, as captured by my buddy @redlight24fps See the journey I took from tearing my triceps to main eventing WrestleMania. 10 years to the day from being forced to retire. It’s a long road.

node.text: This match has many stories to tell. All three of us had a mission. And that day, I’d like to think we all delivered. This one is special to me. Find out how the most violent match in #wrestlemania history all came together. Now. Streaming on @peacocktv & @wwenetwork
